OL,3,CMass graves shed new light on 'dark
OL,4,Cchapter' in city's history
OL,6,FArchaeologists have found a
OL,7,Fsignificant number of graves, dating
OL,8,Fback to the mid-to-late 19th century.
OL,9,FSome burials may even date back to the
OL,10,Fsite's earlier function as a prisoner-
OL,11,Fof-war camp.
OL,13,FCotswold Archaeology has been leading
OL,14,Fthe excavations between 2018 and 2023,
OL,15,Fin consultation with Bristol City
OL,16,FCouncil and the Diocese of Bristol.
OL,18,FThose involved in the project say the
OL,19,Fsite's history is "as complex as it is
OL,20,Ffascinating".
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G2/7
