OL,4,Cchapter' in city's history
OL,6,FThe site began as Stapleton Prison in
OL,7,Fthe late 18th century, housing
OL,8,Fprisoners of war from Britain's
OL,9,Fconflicts with France, Spain, Holland,
OL,10,Fand the United States.
OL,12,FIt was then transformed during
OL,13,FBristol's 1832 cholera outbreak into a
OL,14,Fhospital, and later converted into the
OL,15,FStapleton Workhouse in 1837.
OL,17,FBy the 20th century, the site evolved
OL,18,Finto Manor Park Hospital, and then
OL,19,FBlackberry Hill Hospital, before
OL,20,Fclosing in 2007 as part of Bristol's
OL,21,FLocal Plan.
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G3/7
