OL,3,CMass graves shed new light on 'dark
OL,4,Cchapter' in city's history
OL,6,F"The workhouse served as a refuge for
OL,7,Fthe city's poor, offering shelter to
OL,8,Fthose who had fallen on hard times.
OL,9,FMany of the individuals buried here
OL,10,Fhad faced extreme poverty and illness
OL,11,Fbefore their deaths.
OL,13,F"Examination of their remains, along
OL,14,Fwith personal items found during
OL,15,Fexcavation, helps archaeologists and
OL,16,Fhistorians piece together their life
OL,17,Fstories`highlighting the societal
OL,18,Fstruggles of the era.
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G5/7
